title: Darwin's Doubt and Intelligent Design - Collection 8
description:
Darwin's Doubt and Intelligent Design - Collection 8:

We have 19 titles here. One of them is an audio book that is more than 166 MB.

-  Bickerton - Adam's Tongue; How Humans Made Language, How Language Made Humans (2009)

-  Brinkworth & Weinert (Eds.) - Evolution 2.0; Implications of Darwinism in Philosophy and the Social and Natural Sciences (2012)

-  Collins - The Language of God; a Scientist Presents Evidence for Belief (2006)

-  Davies - The Artful Species; Aesthetics, Art, and Evolution (2012)

-  Kunz - Do Species Exist; Principles of Taxonomic Classification (2012)

-  Leslie - Universes (1989)

-  Martinez - The Mysterious Origins of Hybrid Man; Crossbreeding and the Unexpected Family Tree of Humanity (2013)

-  Miller - Finding Darwin's God; A Scientist's Search for Common Ground between God and Evolution (1999)

-  O'Hear - Beyond Evolution; Human Nature and the Limits of Evolutionary Explanation (1997)

-  Parrington - The Deeper Genome; Why There is More to the Human Genome Than Meets the Eye (2015)

-  Phy-Olsen - Evolution, Creationism, and Intelligent Design (2010)

-  Shapiro - Evolution; a View from the 21st Century (2011)

-  Stannard - Science and the Renewal of Belief (2004)

-  Stove - Darwinian Fairytales (1995)

-  Strick - Sparks of Life; Darwinism and the Victorian Debates over Spontaneous Generation (2000)

-  The Politically Incorrect Guide to Darwinism [audio book]

-  Yahya - Confessions of the Evolutionists (2011)

-  Yahya - The Evolution Impasse, Vol. 1
